en.purpose: For the recording of name details aligned with corresponding FHIR resource.
en.use:
Use to record name details aligned with the corresponding FHIR resources.

This cluster archetype is intended to be used inside FHIR resource aligned archetypes such as CLUSTER.fhir_contact.v0 and CLUSTER.fhir_practitioner.v0.

at0009.1.description: A text representation of the full name.

at0011.2.description: Given name, not always first and includes middle name(s).

at0013.2.description: Part of the name that is acquired as a title due to academic, legal, employment or nobility status, etc. and that appears at the end of the name.

en.purpose: For the recording of telecom details aligned with corresponding FHIR resource.
en.use:
Use to record telecom details aligned with the corresponding FHIR resources.

This cluster archetype is intended to be used inside FHIR resource aligned archetypes such as CLUSTER.fhir_contact.v0 and CLUSTER.fhir_practitioner.v0.

at0002.1.description: The actual contact point details, in a form that is meaningful to the designated communication system (i.e. phone number or email address).

en.purpose: For the recording of organisation details aligned with corresponding FHIR resource.
en.use:
Use to record organisation details aligned with the corresponding FHIR resources.

The slots for telecoms, address and contact should be filled with the appropriate FHIR resource-aligned clusters.

This cluster archetype is intended to be used inside FHIR resource aligned archetypes such as CLUSTER.fhir_contact.v0 and CLUSTER.fhir_practitioner.v0.
